From Satu Laksela [satu.laksela@telia.com]<LINE BREAK>------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------<LINE BREAK>The way to stop the explorer from being an option is to remove it from<LINE BREAK>under the file association for folders. To do this follow these<LINE BREAK>directions.<LINE BREAK><LINE BREAK>Go to My Computer<LINE BREAK>Select View and Options<LINE BREAK>Click on the File Types tab<LINE BREAK>Find the Folder association and double click to open it<LINE BREAK>Highlight explore and click Remove<LINE BREAK><LINE BREAK>This will remove the explorer option from all right mouse button<LINE BREAK>calls.<LINE BREAK><LINE BREAK>The next area to look at is to give the everyone group Execute rights<LINE BREAK>only to explorer.exe command. This will allow explorer to run for the<LINE BREAK>desktop but it will not be available to be added by embedding it into<LINE BREAK>a Word or Excel document.

Check Point Integrity Client versions 4.5.122.000 and 5.1.556.166 are available to fix this issue as well.  Users may download updates automatically or manually from the vendor.
